caption.text:
Getting Millions of Views on Social Media IS NOT luck. And Ill show you my exact strategy in just a couple of hours!

In the last 100 days I used these strategies to grow my Instagram at a rate of about 1700 followers per day for 100 Days in a row. (some days hit 6000 followers in a day )

But Ive also taught all my students how to do it too.

Like:

 Maddy who got a 1 Million view video within her first 3 posts.

 Mitch and Steve who got 9.3 Million views and 150,000 followers within their first week.

And we cover how to get results like this In the Part-Time Creator Academy.

We cover:
The algorithm secrets that make your posts go viral every single time!
The 4 elements of a viral video that make any video get MILLIONS of views!
How to generate an INFINITE number of viral video ideas!
How to properly post your video so it doesnt get shadow-banned!
How to predictably get millions of views on EVERY ONE of your videos!
How to film, edit, and post your videos to maximize their chances of going viral
BONUS:
Confidence on Camera Mini Course - Where we teach you how to feel confident on camera and film in public

If youre ready to take your content creation to the next level and get millions of views, tap learn more below

caption.text:
Have you ever wondered what Green Entrepreneurship really means? 

Maybe the first things that came to mind were planting trees, recycling, or working directly with nature. Or maybe you thought its only for those who want to save the world or that its less profitable than traditional businesses.

But lets take a step back
Its not just a green image, but real solutions to the problems created by todays extractive and polluting economic systems.

In the second episode of the Green Entrepreneurship Series with Najlaa Abdellatif, founder of Zero Waste Palestine, we dive into what green entrepreneurship truly is, explore innovative business models, and discover inspiring examples of Palestinian startups.

And if you also want to learn about the risks of greenwashing and how to distinguish real environmental entrepreneurship from misleading marketing, watch Episode 2 now on YouTube and see how you can be part of the solution!

 Watch the full episode on our YouTube channel.

The Green Forward programme is funded by the European Union and is implemented at the meso level by SPARK and Flow Accelerator in Palestine to foster a green and circular economy (GCE) in the Southern Neighbourhood region.
